# SybaKiller / Project Oodi

## Sovereign split (see `sovereign-hft-architecture.mdc`)
- `execution-engine/` — Rust weapon (HDC, AF_XDP, FIX). No Python on hot path.
- `alpha-swarm/` — Python research only; outputs `hdc_masks.json`.
- `sybakiller/` + `api/` — control plane (admin, testnet).

## Architecture
- Pipeline: market data ingest → order book / state → strategy → risk → gateway → exchange adapter.
- Hot path: no blocking I/O, no heap alloc per tick where avoidable, no unnecessary copies.
- Control plane (FastAPI, admin) stays off the hot path.

## Stack
- Python 3.11+, strict type hints, PEP 8.
- FastAPI for HTTP control plane only.
- JAX only for offline batch/backtest unless profiled on live path.

## Code quality
- No placeholder snippets (`...`, `pass # TODO` in production modules).
- Risk checks before any outbound order; idempotent cancel/replace.
- Never log API keys or full sensitive order payloads.
